│ The `scheduleBlock` function is responsible for scheduling instructions within a block. It ensures that instructions are moved to their appropriate positions while maintaining the dependencies and order        │
│ required for correctness. The dominance issue may arise if instructions are moved in a way that violates dominance rules.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To address this, we need to add a check to ensure that instructions are only moved to positions where they dominate all their uses. This can be done by verifying the dominance relationship before performing    │
│ the `moveAfter` operation.                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ I will now implement this fix by adding dominance checks before moving instructions.                                                                                                                              │
