│ The `reorderInputsAccordingToOpcode` function is responsible for reordering the operands of instructions in the vectorization list (`VL`). It uses the `VLOperands` class to perform the reordering and then      │
│ assigns the reordered operands to `Left` and `Right`.                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ The dominance issue may arise if the reordering process does not respect the dominance constraints of the IR. Specifically, the reordered operands must still dominate their uses after reordering.               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ To address this, we need to ensure that the reordering process checks for dominance violations. I will now investigate the `VLOperands::reorder` function to understand how the reordering is performed and where │
│ dominance checks can be added.                                                                                                                                                                                    │
